WEBVTT

00:00:01.199 --> 00:00:07.879
I am delighted to address Jehovah's people and their friends worldwide today.

00:00:07.879 --> 00:00:15.240
After sundown, some 20 million of us will have gathered in various congregations, groups,

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:21.239
and even as individuals to commemorate the death of Jesus.

00:00:21.239 --> 00:00:28.000
Before we begin our discussion, we will have the text for today read by Brother Don Gordon,

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.920
a helper to the publishing committee.

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:35.399
Today is Tuesday, April 4th.

00:00:35.399 --> 00:00:38.479
Keep doing this in remembrance of me.

00:00:38.479 --> 00:00:42.399
Luke 22, verse 19.

00:00:42.399 --> 00:00:47.479
Why would over 20 million people gather together this evening?

00:00:47.479 --> 00:00:53.759
One reason is our scripture text for today, Luke 22, 19.

00:00:53.759 --> 00:00:59.159
Jesus was in the process of inaugurating the memorial of his death.

00:00:59.159 --> 00:01:05.799
He had just broken the unleavened bread and passed it to each one present.

00:01:05.799 --> 00:01:13.280
The unleavened bread pictured Jesus' perfect, sinless body that he would surrender in death

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:19.680
for the everlasting benefit to all exercising faith in him.

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:26.159
It is at this point that Jesus said the words of Luke 22, 19.

00:01:26.159 --> 00:01:34.400
Keep doing this in remembrance of me, meaning keep using the wine and bread as the way to

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:38.719
remember my death, and all that it will accomplish.

00:01:38.719 --> 00:01:40.760
Why would he say that?

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:43.040
Keep doing this.

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:45.879
He meant exactly what he said.

00:01:45.879 --> 00:01:47.359
Keep doing this.

00:01:47.760 --> 00:01:52.760
Yes, keep doing it on and into the future.

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:56.959
How often did he intend that we keep doing it?

00:01:56.959 --> 00:02:00.760
Some religions partake of the bread and wine weekly.

00:02:00.760 --> 00:02:03.640
They call it communion.

00:02:03.640 --> 00:02:10.639
Other religions let the individual congregations determine how often they would perform this activity.

00:02:10.639 --> 00:02:17.240
Still others instruct that it should be done four times a year.

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:23.080
Why do Jehovah's Witnesses remember Jesus' death in this special way, just once each

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:27.759
year on the anniversary of Jesus' death?

00:02:27.759 --> 00:02:33.719
Well there is some logic to celebrating an anniversary annually on the precise date

00:02:33.719 --> 00:02:38.759
of the original event, much like a wedding anniversary.

00:02:38.759 --> 00:02:45.240
Why would you celebrate a wedding anniversary on any other day of the year, or multiple

00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:47.560
times a year?

00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:54.080
Certainly you would not celebrate your wedding anniversary every week or every day.

00:02:54.080 --> 00:03:04.199
Interestingly, the English word anniversary is defined as the annual recurrence of a date

00:03:04.199 --> 00:03:10.080
marking an event or occurrence of notable importance.

00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:15.909
Jesus' death is certainly of notable importance.

00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:22.550
However, not only is it logical to do so once a year, there is a biblical indication that

00:03:22.550 --> 00:03:32.150
this is what Jesus was requesting in effect saying, keep doing this once a year on the anniversary

00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:37.349
of my death in remembrance of me.

00:03:37.349 --> 00:03:43.949
What is the biblical indication that it should be memorialized just once a year?

00:03:43.949 --> 00:03:47.509
Let's look at the context of our text for today.

00:03:47.509 --> 00:03:53.479
In Luke chapter 22, please locate that text.

00:03:53.479 --> 00:04:02.199
Our day's text is verse 19, but what was the initial purpose of Jesus and His apostles

00:04:02.199 --> 00:04:06.840
gathering together for a meal on that date?

00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:14.159
The date was nice and 14th, according to the Jewish or lunar calendar of that time.

00:04:14.159 --> 00:04:17.399
Please look at Luke 22, 7 and 8.

00:04:17.399 --> 00:04:25.879
It says, the day of the unleavened bread now arrived on which the Passover sacrifice

00:04:25.879 --> 00:04:27.720
must be offered.

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:36.360
So Jesus sent Peter and John, saying, go and get the Passover ready for us to eat.

00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:42.720
According to Jewish law at the time, Jesus had faithfully observed the Passover once

00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:44.720
each year.

00:04:44.720 --> 00:04:49.720
Now, read verses 14 through 17.

00:04:49.720 --> 00:04:55.439
So when the hour came, he reclined at the table along with the apostles, and he said to

00:04:55.439 --> 00:05:04.160
them, I have greatly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer.

00:05:04.160 --> 00:05:12.040
