00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:34.839
read in verse 14 through 17.

00:05:34.839 --> 00:05:41.500
By the time of the first century, it was the custom to pass four cups of wine to those

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:44.500
seated for the Passover meal.

00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:52.740
The cup mentioned in verse 17 was likely the third cup of the Passover celebration.

00:05:52.740 --> 00:06:01.899
Evidently, Jesus was saving the fourth cup for instituting the memorial of his dad.

00:06:01.899 --> 00:06:10.500
So the question is, how often was the Passover to be celebrated?

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:17.199
In Exodus chapter 12, when Jehovah was preparing the Israelites to depart Egypt, he instituted

00:06:17.199 --> 00:06:23.819
the Passover to remember this event of notable importance for the nation.

00:06:23.819 --> 00:06:33.579
At Exodus chapter 12, verse 14, Jehovah instructed Moses, this day will serve as a memorial

00:06:33.579 --> 00:06:41.839
for you, and you must celebrate it as a festival to Jehovah throughout your generations,

00:06:41.839 --> 00:06:47.459
as a lasting statute you should celebrate it.

00:06:47.459 --> 00:06:56.819
He repeated in verse 17, and you must keep this day throughout your generations as a lasting

00:06:56.819 --> 00:06:57.819
statute.

00:06:57.819 --> 00:07:06.379
So it is that Jews observed the Passover once a year as a memorial on the annual anniversary

00:07:06.379 --> 00:07:09.339
of their Exodus from Egypt.

00:07:09.339 --> 00:07:15.540
So after celebrating the last of valid Jewish Passover, when Jesus instituted the memorial

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:22.860
of his death, and he said, keep doing this, his apostles would have known the intent.

00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:28.920
Instead of observing the Passover once a year on that date, they would now remember the

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:33.779
death of Jesus once a year on that same date.

00:07:33.779 --> 00:07:40.379
That seems pretty logical, straightforward, and has a scriptural precedent.

00:07:40.379 --> 00:07:46.540
But many phenomenal Christian religions seem to think memorializing the event more often

00:07:46.540 --> 00:07:50.500
during the year must be even better.

00:07:50.500 --> 00:07:58.500
One part, this is because of a misunderstanding of the intent of 1 Corinthians 11, 25.

00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:03.740
